'''Animesh''' is a [[Hindu]] male first name, meaning "open eyed". 
It is from [[Sanskrit]] ''animi&#7779;a'' "unblinking, vigilant", the name of a [[Deva]], and said of a [[fish]].  The word's [[etymology]] is [[privative a]] + ''ni-mi&#7779;a'' "twinkling" (said of [[Vishnu]], and the name of a son of [[Garuda]]); ''ni-mi&#7779;a'' in turn is from ''mi&#7779;a'' "false appearance".